description: The Knesset passed a bill in its first reading to establish a special commission of inquiry into the failures of October 7, in line with the wishes of Benjamin Netanyahu, who has rejected the idea of a more independent body. However, he now faces difficulties over his advisers' ties to Qatar.

description: Claudia Heiss, a political scientist at the University of Chile, analyzes the factors behind the popular vote that brought the ultra-conservative José Antonio Kast to power on December 14.

headline: The flights of fancy of the French entrepreneur who brought Shein to Paris
description: Since bringing Chinese retail giant Shein to Paris's BHV department store, Frédéric Merlin has faced a barrage of criticism. Presenting himself as a self-made man from a middle-class background, in reality the 34-year-old is thriving on lucrative real estate deals and unpaid debts.

headline: How the Swiss Alps are pushing higher to preserve access to snow
description: Zermatt, the famous ski resort at the foot of the Matterhorn, has invested hundreds of millions of Swiss francs to ensure skiing for its customers nearly year-round, despite global warming. It is a relentless strategy – criticized, but profitable.

headline: Dining at Pierre Soulages' table
description: 'A Meal at the Museum' (1/6). In the southern region of Aveyron, Christophe Chaillou, the chef of Café Bras adjoining the Musée Soulages, prepares fresh, local cuisine shaped by market offerings.

description: The perfume sector is experiencing a global consumption revolution: Young people are collecting bottles, and Chinese consumers are buying more and more. With L'Oréal leading the way, perfume has become the main sector driving the cosmetics industry.

headline: Mariupol, Ukraine: A model city of 'new Russia'
description: Since 2015, photographer Gabriele Micalizzi has been documenting the Donbas region from the Russian side of the front line, an area where Moscow enforces very strict access conditions for journalists. In November, he secured permission to enter Donetsk Oblast, a region of occupied Ukraine, and traveled to Mariupol, a city destroyed by Russian forces in 2022, which has since been colonized and rebuilt in record time.

headline: Why more young people are turning to religion
description: Many researchers have observed a resurgence of religious commitment among young people in France, often accompanied by a certain rigorism. This renewed spiritual quest is linked both to the anxieties of our era and, at times, a search for identity.
